743a17a1-fc4e-434d-ab64-e019aa9450b5.description: Aree are the ocean fairies that are born from the fruits of the World Tree that grows in the center of Aqua World. 8b1a1dc0-f2a4-4f96-b831-b456be0ddc8b.name: Mythical Buddies
8b1a1dc0-f2a4-4f96-b831-b456be0ddc8b.description: In the far reaches of the eastern continent atop the highest hills, I found myself lost for weeks in an unfathomably sprawling woodland. My Buddy companion had long run off somewhere, and I was left alone with no internet, no battery and no water. By chance, I stumbled across a magical spring littered with flower petals. It was then, I heard a voice: Is this your Buddy? A Purrfyn emerges from the brush, to my confusion, before disappearing again. Or this is your Buddy? An Aqumas head pops out of the water before diving just as quick. It was the last thing I remembered before everything faded to white. I awoke later, in a nearby base camp. I was told that my Buddy had come to them for help and led them to me. I looked down to find a peculiarly colored Aquma carrying the scent of tea. How strange, I thought to myself, my Buddy was a Chukwa. (The diary of a bewildered researcher - NEXUS Research Society)

4920cdd8-5606-408b-b44b-bb13836cd2f8.name: Nexus World Land
4920cdd8-5606-408b-b44b-bb13836cd2f8.description: View this lands exact location here : https://maps.affyn.com/8a28347597b7fff Fields of grass, lush forests, vibrant plant life. Of the 4 known biomes of NEXUS World, the Grass Land are the most bountiful and hospitable to life. They aren't very different from tropical environments from our own world apart from the vast differences in plant species. With an abundant selection of plants, food and resources, these areas make great first places to explore for any NEXUS World explorer. Artwork map from OpenStreetMap (https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright)
